<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:abv="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Abaev Dictionary: entry <hi rendition="#rend_italic">bīræ</hi></title></titleStmt><xi:include href="../pubstmt.xml" parse="xml"/><sourceDesc><bibl xml:lang="ru"><author>Абаев, Василий Иванович</author>.
                                <title>Историко-этимологический словарь осетинского языка</title>.
                            Т. <biblScope unit="volume">I</biblScope>. A–Kʼ.
                                <pubPlace>М.–Л.</pubPlace>: <publisher>Наука</publisher>,
                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_bīræ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bīræ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>beræ</orth><form type="variant"><orth>bewræ</orth></form></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>много</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>much</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>многий</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>many</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>долго</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>for a long time</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>очень</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>very</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>bīræ qæbatyr læppūtæ ʒy razyndī, bīræ ʒy ssardta ænafon jæ mælæt</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>много оказалось там храбрых юношей, многие нашли там свою безвременную гибель</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>there were many brave young men, many found there their untimely death</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>132</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>dæ fos bīræ!</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>да умножится твой скот</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>may your cattle multiply!</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>beretæ ni maxæj dær eške ajjepp winag æj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>многие из нас также охотно замечают чужой недостаток</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>many of us also willingly notice another's defect</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>cudan colaqi beremæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нас было много на челне</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>there were many of us on the boat</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>beræ fæxxwæstæncæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>долго они боролись</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>they were fighting for a long time</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>9%l11%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>dæ læg dæ beræ wærzuj?</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>муж тебя очень любит?</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>does your husband loves you very much?</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>11%l2%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*baivar-</w></mentioned>. Хорошо представлено в %bскифских%b собственных именах: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Βαιορααπος</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-aspa-</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-aspa-</w></mentioned></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><w>Βαιορμαιος</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-māya-</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-māya-</w></mentioned></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><w>Όυμβηυαροζ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>xumbewræ</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>xumbewræ</w></mentioned></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><w>Βευραζουρια</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>bewræ-ʒoræ</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>bewræ-ʒoræ</w></mentioned></note></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>159</biblScope></bibl>). За пределами скифо-осетинского можно указать: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>bēvar</w> <gloss><q>десять тысяч</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>bēvar</w> <gloss><q>десять тысяч</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>byūra</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>byurru</w> <gloss><q>десять тысяч</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/> <gloss><q>много</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>VIII 121; IX 73</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>baevarə</w> <gloss><q>десять тысяч</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>множество</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Выпадение %iw%i в %ibiræ%i | %iberæ%i, как в -%iimæ%i (окончание союзного падежа) из -%iiwmæ%i, %iqæmæ%i ‘домой’ из %iqæwmæ%i и др. <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/> <w>biur</w> <gloss><q>десять тысяч</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>bewri</w> <gloss><q>много</q></gloss></mentioned> ‘много’ считаются усвоенными из персидского. Однако армянская форма ближе к староиронской *%ibīwræ%i, а грузинская — к современной дигорской <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>bewræ</w></mentioned>, чем обе они — к персидскому <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>bēvar</w></mentioned>, поэтому не исключено, что они усвоены из аланского, как и <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <w>beurə</w> <gloss><q>много</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><w/> <gloss><q>долго</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Трубецкой</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1921, стр. 249</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1921, p. 249</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 56</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*baivar-</w></mentioned>. The word is widespread in %bScythian%b proper names: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Βαιορααπος</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-aspa-</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-aspa-</w></mentioned></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><w>Βαιορμαιος</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-māya-</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*baivar-māya-</w></mentioned></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><w>Όυμβηυαροζ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>xumbewræ</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>xumbewræ</w></mentioned></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><w>Βευραζουρια</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>bewræ-ʒoræ</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>bewræ-ʒoræ</w></mentioned></note></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>159</biblScope></bibl>). Apart from Scythian-Ossetic, the following words are worth mentioning: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>bēvar</w> <gloss><q>ten thousand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>bēvar</w> <gloss><q>ten thousand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>byūra</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>byurru</w> <gloss><q>ten thousand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/> <gloss><q>much</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>VIII 121; IX 73</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>baevarə</w> <gloss><q>ten thousand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>multitude</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The loss of %iw%i in %ibiræ%i | %iberæ%i, like in -%iimæ%i (comitative case ending) from -%iiwmæ%i, %iqæmæ%i ‘home’ from %iqæwmæ%i etc. <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/> <w>biur</w> <gloss><q>ten thousand</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>bewri</w> <gloss><q>much</q></gloss></mentioned> are considered to be adopted from Persian. However, the Armenian form is close to the old Iron *%ibīwræ%i, and the Georgian one is close to the modern Digor <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>bewræ</w></mentioned>, than both of them are close to the Persian <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>bēvar</w></mentioned>, so it is quite possible that these forms were adopted from Alan, like <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <w>beurə</w> <gloss><q>much</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><w/> <gloss><q>for a long time</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Трубецкой</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1921, стр. 249</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1921, p. 249</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 56</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>